The paper deals with the complexity of reachability in two-dimensional vector addition systems with states, which is a topic in computational logic (cs.LO). The use of vectors and states suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and complexity theory (cs.CC). The mention of "pseudo-polynomial length" suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the use of two-dimensional systems suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG).
